Bromus tomentellus

    Authority   Boiss.
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 3930

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A densely growing bunchgrass reaching a height of
   20-70 cm. USES Used for pasture and for erosion control. GROWING PERIOD
   Growing in spring and summer. COMMON NAMES Russian brome grass, Smooth
   mountain brome grass. FURTHER INF Russian brome grass is native of
   western Asia. In nothern Africa and western Asia it can be found at
   elevations between 1000-3400 m.

   Sources
   SOURCES (B. tomentellus Boiss.)
   Kernick M 1978 pp 79-98 [KTMP, TEMP, DRA, TEXT, FER, RAIN, DEP, USE]

